events.title: JVM Con - Hands-on cloud-native Java with MicroProfile
events.description: Ever wondered what makes a cloud-native application “cloud-native”? Ever wondered what the unique challenges are and how best to address them on fully-open Java technologies? In this workshop, you’ll learn what it means to be cloud-native and how that impacts application development. You’ll learn about Eclipse MicroProfile, an industry collaboration defining technologies for the development and management of cloud-native microservices. With a full set of MicroProfile workshop modules available to you, you’ll be able to start with the basics of REST services and progress to more advanced topics, or you can jump right in and develop secure, fault tolerant, configurable and monitorable microservices. Once you’ve developed your microservice, you can go ahead to package it in a Docker container and deploy it to a Kubernetes cluster. You can rest assured that your cloud-native microservices will perform well in the cloud.

events.title: Eclipse Rich Client Platform (RCP) Schulung
events.description:
In dieser intensiven Schulung lernen Sie die professionelle Eclipse RCP Entwicklung auf Stand von Eclipse 4.6 kennen. Der Praxisteil liegt bei ca. 50 % und durch viele optionale Bestandteile eignet sich die Schulung sowohl für Eclipse RCP Neulinge wie auch für Entwickler mit Eclipse 3.X RCP Vorkenntnissen. Verwendet wird das neuste Eclipse 4 Programmierinterface (API), wobei auch auf die Migration von Eclipse 3.X RCP Applikationen eingegangen wird.

Falls Sie eine Migration von Eclipse 3.X auf Eclipse 4 planen, bieten wir ebenfalls Eclipse 4 RCP Delta Schulungen an. In dieser Schulung lernen Sie die neuen Konzepte von Eclipse 4 und die Unterschiede zu Eclipse 3.X kennen.

Jenseits der Toolorientierung hat sich Eclipse als Plattform für eine Fülle an Anwendungen einen Namen gemacht. events.title: Stammtisch Braunschweig
events.description:
The first BREDEX Eclipse event of the year is a Stammtisch on 6th March at 7pm.
The topic for the evening is JavaFX. JavaFX is a modern alternative to Swing, and can be used in desktop and in mobile applications due to its support of touch and gestures.
The first part of the evening will consist of a talk about JavaFX: the technology, examples, first experiences from current projects and thoughts on design and automated testing.
After the talk, we'll go to a local restaurant to get some food and drink and chat about the talk and other Eclipse topics.
Registration is free : please send a short email to eclipsestammtisch@bredex.de if you would like to come.

events.description: The course will help you understand how to implement your own application based on the Eclipse 4 platform.
